Speckilatzios
Hildegard Heumann

2 eggs
1/2 lb (250g) margarine
1 cup sugar
3 cups flour
1/4 + cup finely chopped almonds
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp cardamom, powdered or ground
1 tsp cloves, powdered or ground
2 tsp cinnamon

Michael's additions:
a little vanilla
pinch of salt
pinch of nutmeg

Mix margarine, eggs, sugar [and vanilla and almonds].

Mix flour, spices and baking powder.

Add dry mixture into wet a little at a time.  Should be thick.

Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

Roll using flour and cut with cookie cutters.

Sprinkle w/ decorations.

Bake for 10 minutes at 375F.
